FOLLOWING hot on the heels of the troubles within the ANC in KwaZuluNatal, the party s Bojanala regional conference, which was to take place on Sunday, has again been prevented from taking place, following a North West High Court judgment.The conference will not go ahead pending finalisation of the urgent application set down for Friday. A representative for the applicants in the matter, Gabriel Nkgweng, who is also a former regional treasurer, said the latest urgent application was launched on Saturday after the PEC chose to go ahead with the conference.On Sunday, Nkgweng said the 40 applicants were fighting against the conference proceeding due to irregularities , which they believe had taken place in terms of the establishment of branches and a selective audit processes. 7012662TNA REPORTER